column3: Edalene of Crescent Cove seeks help removing debris caught in her nets.
Edalene's trawling nets have become clogged with debris from the sea bottom. Aid her by removing whatever flotsam you can find.
You have picked the nets clean. Speak with Edalene once more.
After expressing her gratitude, Edalene goes on about how the life of a fishwife is one of repairing nets and praying for calm waters and large hauls.
Remove debris from the trawling nets.
Have you some time to spare an old fishwife, friend? I've nets what need tendin', as you can probably tell.
These nets you see hangin' here are used to haul in fish. Problem is, in the doin', they dredge up all manner of junk from the sea bottom.
I'd be grateful if you'd pick any debris from them you might find.
Thank you, dear. That's one less chore what needs seein' to.

I tell you, 'tis no easy thing bein' a fishwife. When not mendin' nets and patchin' sails, I'm prayin' to Llymlaen for still waters and a hearty haul. Still, I wouldn't trade all the hard work for anything.
